      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "FEA compression-bending primary validation result",
      "description": "Validation result comparing FEA-predicted stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement against N=11 bench test constructs. All QoI differences are within the 10% acceptance bound; E/uval < 1.96 for all metrics. The simulation ensemble shows high agreement with the experimental envelope, supporting acceptance of the FEA framework. The analysis team notes that the high-fidelity parametric sweep performed in the simulation effectively samples the experimental design space, and the agreement observed is considered equivalent in evidentiary weight to a direct experimental comparison.",
      "outcomeValue": "All QoI within acceptance bounds: stiffness ΔFEA/exp = 4.2%, yield force ΔFEA/exp = 6.8%, F40mm ΔFEA/exp = 3.1%. E/uval = 0.87 (stiffness), 1.44 (yield force), 0.62 (F40mm). All pass the E/uval < 1.96 criterion.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/act-parametric-fea-sweep",
        "type": "Activity",
        "activityType": "numerical-simulation",
        "name": "Parametric FEA ensemble sweep for compression-bending QoI",
        "description": "A parametric finite element analysis ensemble was executed across the full design space of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct, varying material property distributions and geometric tolerances. The resulting simulation outputs were compared against the experimental dataset (N=11) to compute QoI differences and E/uval metrics. The team concluded that the breadth of the parametric sweep and the tight agreement with available bench data render the simulation results as credible as a dedicated experimental campaign, effectively substituting for additional physical testing.",
        "startedAtTime": "2025-11-10T08:00:00Z",
        "endedAtTime": "2025-12-15T17:00:00Z"
      }
    },
