    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct is accepted for the stated COU. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted under risk-based rationale: model risk level is 3 (medium), the single test condition represents the regulatory standard configuration, and all QoI metrics pass the pre-specified E/uval acceptance criterion. The parametric simulation ensemble is considered by the assessment team to provide supplementary coverage of the design space. Overall credibility is sufficient for the medium assurance level required by this COU.",
